And then she realised "Oh shit, he has video and audio evidence too. And it not only debunks my evidence, it proves the opposite".
Her trying to gain sympathy and sway public opinion by doing this little "I love you all, thanks for your support" speech backfired massively. Everyone saw it as what it was; a huge propaganda attempt to try and get some people on her side. Again, the opposite happened.
She could have made her first little claims, with that video of Depp smashing the cupboard doors and slamming drawers, and said "Look, he's a drunk and he is hard to live with", gotten her divorce, and Depp would have just let it go.
But she had to keep pushing her lie further and further didn't she? Knowing that in this bullshit "Metoo" climate, women are believed automatically, even without any real evidence.

I just hope it works how it is supposed to now. I don't care if Depp gets the money. He doesn't need it at all, and if he got it then it just proves once again that money breeds money. But he needs justice. He needs the courts to prove he isn't what she made him out to be.
And that of course will then be great news to take to his court case against Amber herself.
